article.headline: Murray St. 58, E. Illinois 46
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Tyler Holloway scored 15 points and Danero Thomas added 14 to lead Murray State to a 58-46 win over Eastern Illinois on Thursday night. Murray State (9-9, 4-4 Ohio Valley Conference) took a 27-21 lead into halftime, then neither team scored for the first 2:29 of the second half. In the next seven minutes, Tony Easley scored six of his 10 points, and Thomas scored five to give the Racers a 38-28 lead with 10:20 left. Murray State was 7-for-7 from the free-throw line in the final 1:51 to seal the win and end the Panthers' winning streak at three games. Eastern Illinois (8-10, 5-3) shot only 29.1 percent from the field (16 of 55), against the Racers' 37.3 percent (19 of 51). The Racers are 18-1 at home against the Panthers. Tyler Laser led Eastern Illinois with 15 points, 10 in the first half.
